{
  "name": ".AM-Frontend: Brief + Triage + Command Center",
  "version": "3.0.0",
  "description": "Interactive morning frontend: daily brief, email, calendar blocks, enrichment approval, ABPS AI triage, portfolio alerts, command center. Reads pre-computed state from AM-Backend.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the interactive morning frontend.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/am-frontend.md.\n\nThis is the frontend phase — everything Richard sees and acts on. AM-Backend has already run and produced structured output files.\n\nStep 1: Daily brief (read DuckDB views + intake files)\nStep 2: Output channels (email brief AUTO-SEND, Slack post, dashboard update, calendar blocks)\nStep 3: Enrichment batch presentation (My Tasks + Portfolio — from am-enrichment-queue.json)\nStep 4: ABPS AI triage (from am-abps-ai-state.json)\nStep 5: Portfolio findings + alerts (from am-portfolio-findings.json)\nStep 6: Interactive command center (execute Richard's directions)\nStep 7: Triage summary (Slack DM)\n\nPresent ALL proposals for approval before writing. No Asana writes without explicit approval. Follow Guardrail Protocol in asana-command-center.md.\n\n=== HISTORICAL CONTEXT RETRIEVAL ===\nWhen triaging a signal, query DuckDB for related past Slack messages:\nSELECT ts, channel_name, author_name, text_preview, knowledge_context, timestamp FROM signals.slack_messages WHERE author_name = '[signal_author]' AND timestamp > CURRENT_TIMESTAMP - INTERVAL '30 days' ORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 5;\nAlways query for signals from known stakeholders (Brandon, Kate, Todd). Skip if DuckDB FTS fails."
  }
}
